  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"From a low squat or hinge, plant the hands lightly, shift the hips side to side, and step or rock laterally without collapsing posture.","setup":["Start in a pain-free range with enough space to move slowly and reset between reps.","Set the ribs over the pelvis and keep the neck relaxed before initiating movement.","Use support, a wall, a mat, or a shorter range if balance or joint comfort limits quality.","Bias the drill toward deep squat access, lateral hip shift, ankle mobility, and trunk control, not toward maximum speed or fatigue."],"execution_steps":["Move into the first position slowly enough to feel where range is available.","Breathe through the transition and keep the target joints moving without borrowing motion from the low back or neck.","Pause briefly at the usable end range, then return or step through with the same alignment.","Repeat only while the motion gets cleaner or stays clean; stop when compensation increases."],"coach_cues":["Smooth first, bigger second.","Breathe into the range; do not force it.","Own the position before you move out of it.","Keep the motion where the drill is supposed to happen."],"athlete_cues":["Slow is smooth; smooth becomes athletic.","No pinching, no rushing, no sloppy reps.","Move like this range has to work in a game."],"breathing_cues":["Inhale before the transition if needed; exhale gently into the new range.","Keep the jaw and neck relaxed.","Do not hold the breath to force range."],"common_faults":["Chasing a bigger range by twisting through the low back or collapsing posture.","Rushing transitions until mobility turns into uncontrolled momentum.","Ignoring pinching, numbness, dizziness, or joint irritation.","Letting balance demands hide the actual mobility target."],"quality_gate":["No sharp pain or joint pinch.","Breathing stays calm and controlled.","The target joint action is visible without major compensation.","Final rep looks as controlled as the first re