  ('traveling-ape-reach', 'The drill exposes lateral hip mobility, shoulder support, trunk rotation, and playful athletic rhythm while the athlete is actively controlling posture, breathing, and transitions. That turns available range into sport-usable mobility instead of passive flexibility that disappears once movement speed increases.', 'Belongs in Prepare & Access / Mobilize because it increases movement access and readiness before intensity, load, sprinting, cutting, jumping, tumbling, or gameplay. It should not create meaningful fatigue before Output or skill work.', 'Prepare & Access phase after a brief temperature raise and before higher-intent skill, speed, strength, or sport work that needs lateral hip mobility, shoulder support, trunk rotation, and playful athletic rhythm.', 'Rushing for reps, forcing end range through pinching, or turning the drill into a conditioning station. The goal is smoother access and control, not exhaustion or passive stretching for time.', 'Scale by range, support, tempo, and total volume before adding complexity. Athletes should keep breathing, alignment, and repeatable motion as the progression standard.'),
  ('ground-to-stand-mobility-flow', 'The drill exposes hip rotation, trunk control, shoulder support, and athletic transition ability while the athlete is actively controlling posture, breathing, and transitions. That turns available range into sport-usable mobility instead of passive flexibility that disappears once movement speed increases.', 'Belongs in Prepare & Access / Mobilize because it increases movement access and readiness before intensity, load, sprinting, cutting, jumping, tumbling, or gameplay. It should not create meaningful fatigue before Output or skill work.', 'Prepare & Access phase after a brief temperature raise and before higher-intent skill, speed, strength, or sport work that needs hip rotation, trunk control, shoulder support, and athletic transition ability.', 'Rushing for reps, forcing end range through pinching, or turning the drill into a conditioning station. The goal is smoother access and control, not exhaustion or passive stretching for time.', 'Scale by range, support, tempo, and total volume before adding complexity. Athletes should keep breathing, alignment, and repeatable motion as the progression standard.')
